    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;My copy of &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.talesofthefroggod.com/"&gt;Frog God Games&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.talesofthefroggod.com/index.php/products/the-tome-of-horrors"&gt;The Tome of Horrors Complete&lt;/a&gt;, for
&lt;a class="reference external" href="http://www.swordsandwizardry.com/"&gt;Swords &amp;amp; Wizardry&lt;/a&gt;, arrived today.  My, that's a massive tome: a
hardback with 671 numbered pages followed by 14 pages of
advertisements.  (In a smaller book, I might have complained about
that many pages of advertisements, but in a book this large it doesn't
seem excessive.)  From my earlier quick perusal of the PDF and a brief
scan of the hardback today I'm very pleased with the content, and I'm
looking forward to using this in my game.  To the folks who worked on
this: well done!&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
